    <title >Adding and Maintaining Routes for a VXLAN Network</title>
    <shortdesc >You can add or delete routing table entries for hosts on a VXLAN
        network using the CLI.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author >Jim Owens</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <prereq id="prereq_N1001F_N1001C_N10001" >
            <p >The compute node must be locked.</p>
        </prereq>
        <context id="context_N1002D_N1001F_N10001" >
            <p >To add routes, use the following command.</p>
            <codeblock ><systemoutput >~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput >system host-route-add <varname >node</varname> <varname >ifname</varname> <varname >network</varname> <varname >prefix</varname> <varname >gateway</varname> <varname >metric</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <p >where</p>
            <parml>
                <plentry >
                    <pt >node</pt>
                    <pd >
                        <p >is the name or UUID of the compute node</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry >
                    <pt >ifname</pt>
                    <pd >
                        <p >is the name of the interface</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry >
                    <pt >network</pt>
                    <pd >
                        <p >is an IPv4 or IPv6 network address</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry >
                    <pt >prefix</pt>
                    <pd >
                        <p >is the netmask length for the network address</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry >
                    <pt >gateway</pt>
                    <pd >
                        <p >is the default gateway</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry >
                    <pt >metric</pt>
                    <pd >
                        <p >is the cost of the route (the number of hops)</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
            </parml>
            <p >To delete routes, use the following command.</p>
            <codeblock ><systemoutput >~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput >system host-route-delete <varname >uuid</varname> <varname >ifname</varname> <varname >network</varname> <varname >prefix</varname> <varname >gateway</varname> <varname >metric</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <p >where <codeph >uuid</codeph> is the UUID of the route to be deleted.</p>
            <p >To list existing routes, including their UUIDs, use the following command.</p>
            <codeblock ><systemoutput >~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput >system host-route-list compute-0</userinput></codeblock>
        </context>
    </taskbody>
</task-wr>